verbose_text: Over the recent years, it has been suggested that casein kinase 2 interaction protein 1 (CKIP-1) may be the negative regulatory factor of TGF-beta 1 and may play a regulatory role in wound healing [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], providing a new idea for us to learn how to reduce the expression of TGF-beta 1 in the late stage of prostatic urethra wound.
